---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<Layout title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} lastUpdatedFile="src/pages/index.astro">
  <style>
    h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: #222;
    }

    .actions {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .actions a {
      color: inherit;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .actions a::before {
      content: '→ ';
      font-style: normal;
    }

    .actions a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>

  <h1>Grappling is infinitely complex.</h1>

  <p>
    No document, no course, no system can capture it completely. That isn't a problem to solve
    — it's the starting point.
  </p>

  <p>
    Fractal BJJ is an attempt to map high-level No-Gi grappling within a structured repository, in a way a practitioner could actually think about it in real time. The full game is broken into 19 systems, each with an underlying framework of subsystems, concepts and principles.
  </p>

  <p>
    This site is how I organise the sport. It's a working document — built from training,
    teaching, competition, and the best available sources. Always in progress, never final.
  </p>

  <nav class="actions">
    <a href="/systems">Enter the system map</a>
    <a href="/approach">Read the full approach</a>
  </nav>


  <h2>Why FRACTAL?</h2>

  <p>
    Pure mathematical fractals are visualisable patterns of infinite complexity, defined by detailed, self-similar elements that repeat forever at any scale. They are generated by iterating simple mathematical rules, creating structures where zooming in reveals never-ending new, complex details.
  </p>

  <p>
    Sound familiar?
  </p>

</Layout>
